      <h3>How We Evaluated ACV Gummies for Weight Loss</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Reviewed clinical evidence.</strong> We analyzed every published RCT and meta-analysis on ACV and weight management, body composition, and blood sugar regulation to establish the evidence-based claims threshold.</li>
        <li><strong>Calculated acetic acid content.</strong> We estimated the acetic acid content of each product based on ACV concentration and cross-referenced with any available certificates of analysis to assess dose adequacy against clinical benchmarks.</li>
        <li><strong>Evaluated complementary ingredients.</strong> Products containing B-vitamins, iodine, chromium, or other metabolism-supporting nutrients received higher scores than ACV-only formulas.</li>
        <li><strong>Verified third-party testing.</strong> We contacted manufacturers to confirm independent testing and checked ConsumerLab reports for ACV gummy accuracy data.</li>
        <li><strong>Assessed long-term value.</strong> We calculated cost per day and cost per 12-week cycle (the minimum study duration for weight management outcomes).</li>
