      <p>Take ACV gummies 15-30 minutes before your largest meal, maintain a consistent daily routine for at least 12 weeks, and pair supplementation with a modest caloric deficit for the best results.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About ACV Gummies and Weight Loss</h2>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Do ACV gummies really help with weight loss?</summary>
      <p>ACV gummies may provide modest weight management support. A 2018 study found that daily ACV consumption reduced body weight by 2-4 pounds over 12 weeks alongside a calorie-restricted diet. The mechanism involves AMPK activation (increased fat oxidation), blood sugar regulation, and increased satiety. ACV is a complementary tool, not a standalone solution.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How much ACV should I take daily for weight loss?</summary>
      <p>Clinical studies used 15-30mL of liquid ACV (750-1500mg acetic acid) daily. Most ACV gummies provide 500mg of ACV per serving (approximately 250-500mg acetic acid). To approximate the studied dose, you may need 2-3 servings daily or choose higher-potency products like Flat Tummy (1000mg per serving).</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is the best time to take ACV gummies?</summary>
      <p>Take 15-30 minutes before your largest meal. Acetic acid consumed before meals reduces postprandial blood sugar spikes by 20-30% and increases satiety, reducing caloric intake by 200-275 calories over the remainder of the day.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Are ACV gummies better than liquid ACV?</summary>
      <p>Liquid ACV is more potent and cheaper but risks tooth enamel erosion and esophageal irritation. Gummies are safer, taste better, and drive higher daily compliance — which matters more than per-serving potency over a 12-week weight management period.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Can ACV gummies cause side effects?</summary>
      <p>The most common side effect is mild digestive discomfort when taken on an empty stomach. ACV may interact with diabetes medications, diuretics, and digoxin. Individuals with gastroparesis should avoid ACV. The added sugar (2-4g per serving) is nutritionally insignificant.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How long do ACV gummies take to work?</summary>
      <p>Blood sugar and appetite effects occur within 30-60 minutes. Measurable weight loss requires 8-12 weeks of consistent daily use alongside dietary changes. The 2018 RCT observed statistically significant weight reduction at the 12-week mark.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What should I look for in an ACV gummy?</summary>
      <p>At least 500mg ACV per serving, acetic acid content specified, unfiltered ACV with the "mother," third-party testing, and complementary metabolic ingredients like B-vitamins or iodine. Avoid products making dramatic weight loss claims unsupported by clinical evidence.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Are ACV gummies safe during pregnancy?</summary>
      <p>There is insufficient safety data for ACV supplementation during pregnancy. Small amounts of ACV in food are generally considered safe, but concentrated supplements have not been studied. Consult your obstetrician before taking any ACV supplement during pregnancy or breastfeeding.</p>
    </details>

